# Headless notification modules (`*.core.js`)

Android capture registers in `apps/mobile/index.js` **before** expo-router. That entry and Node suites (`scripts/*-suite.mjs`) `require()` plain CommonJS — do not duplicate the same logic in TypeScript.

## Pattern

| File | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `foo.core.js` | **Only** implementation — CommonJS `module.exports` |
| `foo.ts` | Thin typed re-export / facade for `@/lib/notifications/foo`; app-only extras allowed here |

- `index.js` and suites: `require('…/*.core')` or `…/*.core.js`
- App/TS: import the `.ts` module (no `.core` in the path)
- Keep `.core.js` free of Legend-State, expo-router, and UI imports

## Anti-patterns

- `foo.js` + `foo.ts` with the same algorithms
- Naming the CommonJS file `foo.js` next to `foo.ts` (ambiguous Metro/TS resolve) — always `foo.core.js`
- Putting store/UI-only code in `.core.js` — e.g. `refreshLinkedPackagesFromStore` stays in `.ts`; headless reads stay in `.core.js`
